ria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/syamkumar\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/abfa8cdc3ab8d512b073943694844899?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/abfa8cdc3ab8d512b073943694844899?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/syamkumar\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Syam Kumar R <small>(syamkumar)<\/small><\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">February 24, 2018<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">I recently upgraded my VPS. After that I was unable to update plugins using SSH2. I was getting this error : \"Unable to locate WordPress Content directory (wp-content)\". This plugin fixed the problem. Just put the plugin files in the plugins folder, enabled the plugin from admin area. Everything started working!<\/div>\n<\/div>\n"
